TM17-159 — Reporting Page Filter & Sorting Cleanup / De-hardcoding

Overview

This update refactors the internal filtering, sorting, and option-handling logic within the reporting page to make it more maintainable, less hardcoded, and more consistent across chart, table, and UI rendering paths.

Previously, several parts of the reporting page relied on inline arrays, repeated logic, and implicit ordering rules (for things like label detection, column ordering, and chart rendering). This made the behavior harder to adjust and introduced inconsistency in how data was displayed across charts and tables. This update introduces small, safe abstractions and shared configuration constants to standardize behavior without altering the overall functionality or structure of the page.

The goal of this change is to improve clarity and flexibility while keeping the implementation lightweight and low-risk.

---

1. Frontend Integration — Removal of Hardcoded UI Option Lists

---

Affected component: Reporting page (`ReportingPage`)

Changes made:

* Extracted inline option arrays into reusable constants:

  * `PDF_DISPLAY_OPTIONS`
  * `PDF_LAYOUT_OPTIONS`
  * `SOCIAL_PLATFORMS`
  * `DOWNLOAD_FORMATS`
* Replaced inline `.map()` arrays in JSX with these constants
* Ensured all UI option rendering now pulls from a single source of truth
* Preserved existing UI behavior and structure without introducing new components

Behavior breakdown:

| Area                | Before                    | After                             |
| ------------------- | ------------------------- | --------------------------------- |
| PDF display options | Hardcoded inside JSX      | Driven by `PDF_DISPLAY_OPTIONS`   |
| PDF layout options  | Hardcoded inside JSX      | Driven by `PDF_LAYOUT_OPTIONS`    |
| Social platforms    | Inline array in component | Centralized in `SOCIAL_PLATFORMS` |
| Download formats    | Inline array in JSX       | Centralized in `DOWNLOAD_FORMATS` |

